text: Gordon Laro (born April 17, 1972) is a former American football tight end. Laro played college football at Boston College. He was a member of the Jacksonville Jaguars for their inaugural season in 1995, where he appeared in two games for the team. == References == Category:Living people Category:1972 births Category:American football tight ends Category:Jacksonville Jaguars players Category:Boston College Eagles football players Category:Players of American football from Massachusetts Category:People from Lynn, Massachusetts
